# WebGL2 Feature Detection and Canvas2D Fallback

The EnhancedStimulusRenderer provides automatic WebGL capability detection with graceful degradation to Canvas2D when WebGL is not available. This ensures experiments can run on a wider range of devices while maintaining optimal performance where possible.

## Features

### Automatic Detection
- WebGL2 support (preferred for best performance)
- WebGL1 fallback (when WebGL2 unavailable)
- Canvas2D fallback (when no WebGL available)
- Hardware capability reporting
- Performance monitoring integration

### Renderer Capabilities
```typescript
interface RendererCapabilities {
  webGL2: boolean;
  webGL1: boolean;
  canvas2D: boolean;
  maxTextureSize: number;
  maxRenderBufferSize: number;
  supportedExtensions: string[];
  renderer: 'webgl2' | 'webgl' | 'canvas' | 'unknown';
}
```

## Usage

### Basic Usage with Automatic Detection

```typescript
import { EnhancedStimulusRenderer } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

const renderer = EnhancedStimulusRenderer.getInstance();

// Check capabilities before initialization
const capabilities = renderer.getCapabilities();
console.log('WebGL2 available:', capabilities.webGL2);
console.log('Current renderer:', capabilities.renderer);

// Initialize with automatic detection
await renderer.initialize({
  enableFallback: true,  // Enable Canvas2D fallback
  preferWebGL2: true,    // Prefer WebGL2 over WebGL1
  powerPreference: 'high-performance'
});

// Check if using fallback
if (renderer.isUsingFallback()) {
  console.warn('Running in Canvas2D fallback mode');
}
```

### Force Specific Renderer

```typescript
// Force WebGL1 (skip WebGL2)
await renderer.initialize({
  preferWebGL2: false,
  enableFallback: false
});

// Force Canvas2D fallback
await renderer.initialize({
  enableFallback: true,
  // Simulate WebGL failure for testing
});
```

### Integration with Experiments

```typescript
import { experiment, EnhancedStimulusRenderer } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

experiment('My Experiment')
  .onBeforeStart(async () => {
    const renderer = EnhancedStimulusRenderer.getInstance();
    await renderer.initialize({
      enableFallback: true
    });

    // Warn participants if using fallback
    if (renderer.isUsingFallback()) {
      console.warn('Limited graphics mode - some effects may be reduced');
    }
  })
  .build();
```

## Performance Implications

### WebGL2 (Preferred)
- Full hardware acceleration
- Advanced shader effects
- Texture filtering and transforms
- 144Hz+ display support
- <2ms timing precision possible

### WebGL1 (Fallback 1)
- Hardware acceleration
- Most effects supported
- Some advanced features unavailable
- 60-120Hz typical performance
- Good timing precision

### Canvas2D (Fallback 2)
- Software rendering
- Basic shapes and text only
- No advanced effects (blur, filters)
- 30-60Hz typical performance
- Limited timing precision

## Feature Availability by Renderer

| Feature | WebGL2 | WebGL1 | Canvas2D |
|---------|--------|--------|----------|
| Hardware Acceleration | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ |
| Texture Filters | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ |
| Blur Effects | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ |
| Color Matrix | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ |
| Alpha Blending | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Basic Shapes | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Text Rendering | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Image Display | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Animations | ✅ | ✅ | Limited |
| 144Hz Support | ✅ | Maybe | ❌ |

## Browser Compatibility

### WebGL2 Support (as of 2024)
- Chrome 56+ (2017)
- Firefox 51+ (2017)
- Safari 15+ (2021)
- Edge 79+ (2020)

### WebGL1 Support
- Chrome 9+ (2011)
- Firefox 4+ (2011)
- Safari 5.1+ (2011)
- Edge 12+ (2015)
- IE 11 (limited)

### Canvas2D Support
- All modern browsers
- IE 9+
- Mobile browsers

## Recommendations

### For Researchers
1. Always enable fallback for maximum compatibility
2. Test experiments in fallback mode
3. Document minimum requirements
4. Consider simpler visuals for broader support

### For Developers
1. Use feature detection, not browser detection
2. Implement progressive enhancement
3. Test across renderer modes
4. Monitor performance metrics

### Hardware Requirements
- **Optimal**: Discrete GPU, WebGL2 support
- **Good**: Integrated GPU, WebGL1 support  
- **Minimum**: Any device with Canvas2D

## Testing Fallback Behavior

```typescript
// Force Canvas2D for testing
const originalGetContext = HTMLCanvasElement.prototype.getContext;
HTMLCanvasElement.prototype.getContext = function(contextType: string) {
  if (contextType.includes('webgl')) {
    return null; // Simulate no WebGL
  }
  return originalGetContext.call(this, contextType as any);
};

// Run your experiment
await runExperiment();

// Restore normal behavior
HTMLCanvasElement.prototype.getContext = originalGetContext;
```

## Performance Monitoring

```typescript
const renderer = EnhancedStimulusRenderer.getInstance();
const metrics = renderer.getPerformanceMetrics();

console.log('Current FPS:', metrics.current.fps);
console.log('Average Frame Time:', metrics.average.frameTime);
console.log('Memory Usage:', metrics.current.heapUsed);
```

## Migration from StimulusRenderer

The EnhancedStimulusRenderer is backward compatible with StimulusRenderer:

```typescript
// Old code
const renderer = StimulusRenderer.getInstance();

// New code - drop-in replacement
const renderer = EnhancedStimulusRenderer.getInstance();
```

All existing stimulus types work with both renderers.

