## Testing Fallback Behavior

```typescript
// Force Canvas2D for testing
const originalGetContext = HTMLCanvasElement.prototype.getContext;
HTMLCanvasElement.prototype.getContext = function(contextType: string) {
  if (contextType.includes('webgl')) {
    return null; // Simulate no WebGL
  }
  return originalGetContext.call(this, contextType as any);
};

// Run your experiment
await runExperiment();

// Restore normal behavior
HTMLCanvasElement.prototype.getContext = originalGetContext;
```

## Performance Monitoring

```typescript
const renderer = EnhancedStimulusRenderer.getInstance();
const metrics = renderer.getPerformanceMetrics();

console.log('Current FPS:', metrics.current.fps);
console.log('Average Frame Time:', metrics.average.frameTime);
console.log('Memory Usage:', metrics.current.heapUsed);
```

## Migration from StimulusRenderer

The EnhancedStimulusRenderer is backward compatible with StimulusRenderer:

```typescript
// Old code
const renderer = StimulusRenderer.getInstance();

// New code - drop-in replacement
const renderer = EnhancedStimulusRenderer.getInstance();
```

All existing stimulus types work with both renderers.
